		<div id="comment-12440">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/51042462c6b3d20f5e7ca4eeb1807986?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/51042462c6b3d20f5e7ca4eeb1807986?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Kevin</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>			</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
				
			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-12440">
				September 20, 2012 at 06:01					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>Leticia:</p>
<p>&#8220;Flowers for Algernon&#8221; won the <a href="../../hugo-history/1960-hugo-awards/index.html" rel="nofollow">1960 Hugo Award</a> for Best Short Story. The expanded novel was nominated for the <a href="../../hugo-history/1967-hugo-awards/index.html" rel="nofollow">1967 Hugo Award</a> for Best Novel, but did not win.</p>
<p>The rules of the World Science Fiction Society allow works to be nominated an additional time if they are substantially different, such as after a significant revision or expansion. Both the short story and the novel versions of the the work were nominated for Hugo Awards. The short story won in 1960, and the novel was nominated in 1967. I hope this clarifies the situation for you.</p>
</div>

				<div class="reply">
				<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?replytocom=12440#respond' data-commentid="12440" data-postid="11" data-belowelement="comment-12440" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Kevin'>Reply</a>				</div><!-- .reply -->
