				<div class="comment-body"><p>Hello,<br />
Congratulations on an excellent Hugo Awards night at LoneStarCon, it was my first experience of such a thing and I had a fantastic evening. It was really well run and so lovely to see the winners bounding on stage with such enthusiasm and pride. A wonderful way to celebrate a wonderful genre.<br />
I would like to know if you are considering an improvement to the communications process, in light of Mary Robinette Kowel finding out at the after-party that one of her works had been shortlisted but deemed ineligible? I understand there are difficulties around the categorization of various works and I don&#8217;t have the depth of knowledge to have an opinion at that, but I&#8217;m sure you can understand that this must have been very distressing for her to receive this information in such an unexpected and public way.<br />
Even if the nominee disagrees with your decision, I&#8217;m sure they would greatly prefer to be advised in advance, rather than getting a horrible shock at what is supposed to be a celebratory evening.<br />
Thank you for your consideration.</p>
