				<div class="comment-body"><p>To our knowledge, there has never been a category proposed for non-English-language works. Given the current electorate (the members of the World Science Fiction Society), it seems unlikely that there would be enough nominations to justify the category. However, you might consider contacting a future Worldcon committee and ask them to use their Special Category authority to create a one-time category for such works, in order to judge whether there was sufficient support among the members of WSFS for such a category.</p>
</div>

