				<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/51042462c6b3d20f5e7ca4eeb1807986?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/51042462c6b3d20f5e7ca4eeb1807986?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Kevin</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>			</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
				
			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-437033">
				September 14, 2015 at 09:10					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>Nana:</p>
<p>Assuming that the novella was published in Spanish in 1940, it is eligible for the 1941 Retro-Hugo Award for Best Novella. Works need not be published in English to be eligible for the Hugo Award. When published in English translation, the works get another year of eligibility; thus the work was eligible for the 2004 Hugo Award as well.</p>
</div>

